  "prompt": "What do I feed my 5-month-old Rottweiler?",
  "response": "At 5 months old, your Rottweiler should be on a balanced diet specifically formulated for large breed puppies. Here are some guidelines:\n\n1. Commercial Dog Food\n- Choose high-quality puppy food designed for large breed dogs\n- Look for foods with:\n- High protein content\n- Balanced nutrients\n- No artificial preservatives\n- Appropriate calcium and phosphorus levels\n\n2. Feeding Frequency\n- 3-4 meals per day\n- Gradually transition to 2 meals per day as they approach adulthood\n\n3. Recommended Nutrients\n- Protein: 25-30%\n- Fat: 12-15%\n- Calcium and phosphorus in correct proportions\n\n4. Portion Size\n- Follow packaging recommendations based on weight\n- Typically 2-3 cups per day, divided into multiple meals\n- Monitor weight and adjust accordingly\n\n5. Additional Tips\n- Always provide fresh water\n- Avoid human food\n- No table scraps\n- Introduce treats in moderation\n- Consult your veterinarian for personalized advice\n\n6. Potential Supplements\n- Discuss with your vet if any additional supplements are needed\n\nRemember that individual dogs may have different nutritional needs, so consult your veterinarian for specific recommendations.",
